yield from gives the option to create some sort of "middle-man" generator which
can receive values and pass them to a sub-generator and get the values from him
and yield them to the caller.
# CR: We dont use `send` in generators because it's confusing, and not really useful
It's just a short way of doing:
`yield from x`
is equivalent to
`
for item in x:
    yield item
`
